history.content:
Since many of you have asked about the next offering of CS 191 Quantum Computing (please direct those questions to the instructor, we don't know), you may want to check out Physics 151 - Quantum Information and Computing. 

For prereq/prior experience info, the instructor said the following: "It is not so much the background but rather the mindset. I would say that they should be familiar with atoms and that they have discrete levels. They also should be familiar with eigenvalue problems. Ideally, they have seen the Schrödinger equation."

Course flyer: 151_S18_Course_Flyer2.pdf

The instructor is Professor Hartmut Haeffner - you can contact him if you have any questions
